  "prompt": "Is it true that a fan consumes the same electricity on level 1 (slow) as it does on level 5 (faster)?",
  "response": "No, it is not true that a fan consumes the same amount of electricity on level 1 (slow) as it does on level 5 (faster). In general, an electric fan's power consumption increases with the speed setting. \n\nFans typically use motors that draw more power as the speed increases to generate more airflow. Therefore, higher speed settings typically result in higher electricity consumption compared to lower speed settings. This relationship is not always linear; the exact power usage can depend on the fan's design and technology. \n\nFor accurate information, you should check the specifications or power ratings provided by the manufacturer for the specific fan model.",
